  "body": "Following https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/4743\n\nWe should update all the usages we can to be getByBlockHeader and phase out getByBlockNumber.\n\ngetByBlockNumber can cause issues in a post-shanghai (TimestampSchedule-enabled) chain.\n\nThis has been intentionally separated out of #4743 so it doesn't make the PR huge, see this spike for an idea of what the changes might look like: https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/4687\n\nAnother related item for clean-up:\nhttps://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/4743#discussion_r1045390099\n\nTasks\n- [x] Simple replacements of getByBlockNumber to getByBlockHeader\n- [x] Create getForNextBlock (used in AbstractBlockCreator, PoWMinerExecutor and likely in BFT)\n- [x] Investigate FlexiblePrivacyPrecompiledContract usage in RunnerBuilder.createPrivateTransactionObserver()\n- [x] Handle Dao fork and classic fork in ProtocolScheduleBuilder\n- [x] BFT sequence number usage\n- [x] Change streamMilestoneBlocks to a findSchedule(Predicate) [need to fix usage in TransactionPoolFactory, RunnerBuilder]\n- [x] Consider deleting getByBlockNumber usage in CombinedProtocolScheduleFactory\n- [x] Fix tests to getByBlockHeader or create a test ProtocolSchedule that has getByBlockNumber inc streamMilestoneBlocks for checking milestones\n- [x] ScheduleBasedBlockHeaderFunctions getBlockHeaderFunctions usage of getByBlockNumber\n- [x] CheckpointSyncDownloadPipelineFactory getBlockHeaderFunctions usage of getByBlockNumber\n- [x] Replace HeaderBasedProtocolSchedule with ProtocolSchedule\n",
